  <tex>\{  y  \in  D  \mid  y  \ll  x  \}</tex>.
</p><p>  A subset <tex>B  \subseteq  D</tex> forms a basis for <tex>D</tex> if for every element <tex>x  \in   D</tex> the set <tex display="block">B_x  \vcentcolon \equiv   \Downarrow (x)  \cap  B</tex> contains a directed
  subset with supremum <tex>x</tex></p><p>  Elements of <tex>x</tex> are caled approximants to <tex>x</tex> relative to <tex>B</tex>.
</p><p>  <b>Definition 2.2.3</b> from <link href="samson-abramsky.xml" type="local" title="Abramsky">Abramsky</link> and <link href="achim-jung.xml" type="local" title="Jung">Jung</link>'s
